'From Squeak 2.0 BETA of May 8, 1998 on 8 May 1998 at 9:24:03 pm'!!FileDirectory methodsFor: 'file name utilities' stamp: 'jm 5/8/1998 20:48'!checkName: aFileName fixErrors: fixing	"Check a string aFileName for validity as a file name. Answer the original file name if it is valid. If the name is not valid (e.g., it is too long or contains illegal characters) and fixing is false, raise an error. If fixing is true, fix the name (usually by truncating and/or tranforming characters), and answer the corrected name. The default behavior is just to truncate the name to the maximum length for this platform. Subclasses can do any kind of checking and correction appropriate for their platform."	| maxLength |	aFileName size = 0 ifTrue: [self error: 'zero length file name'].	maxLength _ self class maxFileNameLength.	aFileName size > maxLength ifTrue: [		fixing			ifTrue: [^ aFileName contractTo: maxLength]			ifFalse: [self error: 'file name is too long']].	^ aFileName! !!FileDirectory class methodsFor: 'platform specific' stamp: 'jm 5/8/1998 20:45'!maxFileNameLength	^ 31! !!DosFileDirectory class methodsFor: 'platform specific' stamp: 'jm 5/8/1998 20:45'!maxFileNameLength	^ 255! !